    fix(skills): guardrails §5a + planner verifier hygiene + judge rubric whole-file scoring
    
    Three prompt-level fixes that emerged from running /uteki-review on
    a real-LLM run and applying the critique back to the system. Full
    iteration chain documented in design/02-self-evolution-loop.md.
    
    1. _shared/guardrails.md §5a — "交付物只装成品，不装过程"
       New section forbidding scratchpad / draft attempts / character-
       counting / workflow narration in artifact files. Includes a hard
       "first character must be # or substantive content" rule and a
       short list of forbidden opening phrases ("我来...", "现在直接...",
       "以下不含..."). Note: pure-prompt enforcement found insufficient
       (see fix(artifacts) for the deterministic strip).
    
    2. skills/planner/SKILL.md — verifier hygiene
       - C1 regex changed from `(\d{6}\.(SH|SZ)|[A-Z]{2,5})` to
         `\d{6}\.(SH|SZ)`. The OR branch was matching English words
         (literal observed: "to", "need", "start" — 1187 false matches
         in one run). Loosens to add NASDAQ/NYSE in a separate criterion
         when US names are needed.
       - New "regex_in_text 写法约定" section teaching abstract failure
         patterns WITHOUT showing the bad regex literally (negative-
         example latch hazard — model copies bad pattern from warning).
         Two questions to ask before shipping a regex: false-positive
         on prose? matches multi-line by default?
       - Reinforced "Required criteria" — explicitly says all 5 (C1-C5)
         are mandatory after observing a run where planner dropped C4/C5.
    
    3. eval/judges/{correctness,cite_compliance}.md — whole-file scoring
       Both rubrics now lead with "评分对象：整份 artifact 文件作为单一
       交付物". If the file contains scratchpad / drafts / self-evaluation
       tables, score MUST be ≤ 4 with rationale citing §5a violation.
       Was: judges hallucinated a clean draft inside scratchpad-filled
       files and graded that subset (9/10 in run 1 despite 80% of the
       file being meta-narration).
    
    Plus: .claude/commands/uteki-review.md — frontmatter removed
    because the slash-command discovery in CC 2.1.116 was rejecting it.
    Body content unchanged.
    
    Iteration chain (real-LLM, deepseek+aihubmix, ~$2 total across 7 runs):
      Run 1: 9/8 judges (graded wrong target), revise for wrong reason
      Run 2: 3/3 (judges harshened), still scratchpad
      Run 3: 3/1 (judges caught more violations), still scratchpad
      Runs 4-5: api-restart bookkeeping issues
      Run 6: strip works but planner regressed contract
      Run 7: 9/9, approve, 5/5 criteria passed, file opens with `#` ✓
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

